-- Jeev Milkha Singh Beats Molinari in Playoff at Scottish Open
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-07-15T17:19:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-15/jeev-milkha-singh-beats-molinari-in-playoff-at-scottish-open.html
India’s Jeev Milkha Singh beat
Francesco Molinari of Italy at the first playoff hole to win
golf’s Scottish Open in Inverness today.  The pair had finished level on 17-under par 271 after final
rounds of 67 and 72, respectively. Scotland’s Marc Warren, who
three away a three-shot lead, came joint third on 16-under with
Alexander Noren of Sweden.  The result means Singh qualifies for the British Open,
starting in four days at Royal Lytham & St. Annes in northwest
 England . He picked up a prize of 518,000 euros ($633,000) today
in his fourth win on the European Tour.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 